title: A Mystic Journey (AVENGERS/LOTR)
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2sY4LyR

by TheGarryGuy

AU de Avengers y el Universo de Tolkien. (Señor de los anillos y The Hobbit)

La historia de un pequeño Hobbit quien presenció la guerra mística más bélica de todos los tiempos. “A mystic journey” es el relato más detallado a boca de Everett Ross, el cual cuenta la historia de cómo las legiones de enanos, elfos y hombres combatieron contras las fuerzas oscuras comandadas por Thanos, el rey de Mordor, y cómo la presencia de un hijo hechicero del Padre de Todo cambió la vida de todos y todo en la Tercera Edad de la Tierra Media.

#ironstrange #everstrange #stony #stucky y más.

title: Playlist
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2MC8PxQ

by TenSpencerRiedPlease

He pulls Peter’s phone out of his pocket and Tony snatches it, scrolling through the absurd amount of playlists. “Oh here’s one. ‘That feeling you get when you fuck at three a.m but actually you want to die.’ I don’t know what that means.”

Stephen pulls the phone back and starts scrolling. “Oh lovely- ‘for when you’re in Medicine Hat, Canada and the Tim Hortons is being held up.’ Are these built on personal experience?” he asks, squinting.

Tony takes the phone back and scrolls a little before sighing. “Seriously? ‘The feeling you get when you look at Tony Stark’s ass’? Is that a real thing?”

Stephen takes the phone back and laughs, “it was made three years before he met you,” he says. “That’s funnier.”

He pulls Peter’s phone out of his pocket and Tony snatches it, scrolling through the absurd amount of playlists. “Oh here’s one. ‘That feeling you get when you fuck at three a.m but actually you want to die.’ I don’t know what that means.”

Stephen pulls the phone back and starts scrolling. “Oh lovely- ‘for when you’re in Medicine Hat, Canada and the Tim Hortons is being held up.’ Are these built on personal experience?” he asks, squinting.

Tony takes the phone back and scrolls a little before sighing. “Seriously? ‘The feeling you get when you look at Tony Stark’s ass’? Is that a real thing?”

Stephen takes the phone back and laughs, “it was made three years before he met you,” he says. “That’s funnier.”
